<HTML><HEAD><META NAME="Description" CONTENT="The venerable guild Forgotten Truth, Everquest, expands to Asheron's Call"><META NAME="Keywords" CONTENT="message boards, forum, free forums, free message boards, visual basic, programming, programmers, community, vb, directx, games, dx, basic, bulletin boards, online communities, discussion forums, The, Forgotten, Truth, In, Asheron's, Call"><TITLE>The run to AB! - www.ezboard.com</TITLE></HEAD><BODY TEXT=#ffffff BGCOLOR=#000000 LINK=#70db93 VLINK=#00ff00 ALINK=#FF0000><CENTER><CENTER><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/cscintro.html" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/banners/cscuserbanner.gif"></a></CENTER><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95%><TR><TD><B><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Forgotten Truth Foreign Legion</FONT></A></B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>General</FONT></A></B><BR><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>The run to AB!</FONT></B></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/newTopic1.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; &nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/addReply1.gif border=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showMessage?topicID=306.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showMessage?topicID=305.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>4:04:02 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The run to AB!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">OK...a blow by blow account of my trip as it happens. I started by taking a quick inventory of my equipment. I traded out my leather legs for some yoroi with better elemental protections. Found my best lightning protection ... gold wasps hurt ... and grabbed my skull mask. I wanted to see if the rumor about the skull mask were true so I ran down to the skellie house but they all still jumped me like normal. Oh well. I've lifestoned in Arwic and just tied to the subway portal...I intend to charge a few peeps in AB with a portal to the subway to finance this run. I'm off to Gendon Woods and the north dires portal. I'll keep you posted.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>4:16:58 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Glendon Woods</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I jumped down to the bottom of the subway and took the Glendon Woods portal as planned. In GW, I used the nearest lifestone and then ran south to the North Dires portal. Didn't see much on the way as this is fairly peacful land. At the portal I decided to wait until daylight for the next leg of my journey.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>4:33:50 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Glendon Woods</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This is awesome Crow! Keep up the reports, and good luck!!! Hopefully I'll be able to buy you a beer in the AB tavern tonight... I have a feeling you're going to need it!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>4:46:26 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=3><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Through the portal</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Do you know how boring it is sitting in the middle of nowhere waiting for daylight? Well, I decided to go in the dark...Darktide to be exact. Boy, was I wrong to do so! Coming out of the portal I appeared in the middle of a running battle. 3 people were fighting a whole heard of shadows and assorted monster trash. Spells were flying and even though none were aimed at me I took 2 hits! Down to half-health...I healed quickly and snapped off a few shots. All the while, the brave souls around me were falling. With the last one down I decided that my mission must take priority so I turned and made a hasty retreat. Crossing the 2 inlets leading to the North Dires land bridge, I paused to kill a few frags. As usual ... they dropped nothing. But i did mange to scare up a lone Skellie Bone Lord who was most happy to drop 2 level V debuffs on me!! Now I'm sitting o the landbridge waiting for the buffs to run out. I'll keep you posted as I move into the dires!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>4:54:38 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=4><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Foredawn-and-Half</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Just as first light broke, my debuffs finally ran out. Weakness Other V was the first to go...but the Life Magic Inept. V seemed to linger forever. I've started my buff cycle and will begin the first third of my run soon. I alawys take the smae route to Fort Teth divided into thirds: The LandBridge run, The manuver to the Old Tower, then the Sprint to the Ft. Teth Lifestone. Here goes nothing.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>5:34:51 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=5><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">North Dires &quot;Deathbridge&quot;</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">On somedays the landbridge is pretty easy to cross ... on others it can be a deathtrap! I should have seen the signs but in my excitement to reach AB I wasn't looking to closely. It started with my buff cycle. I burned out 2 golden scarabs in as many tries to start my level V buffs. No worries I thought ... I'll go for IV's. After buffing I noticed 2 blips on radar...2 frags side by side. Not one to pass up an opportunity, I took both down. The lack of shards on either one should have been my first sign ... the 3 gold wasps that spawned next should have been my second! Down to only 22 hitpoints out of 140 something, I was running for my life!! Burst of electricty flying past me to left and right! Golems growing from the very earth itself to bar my path! Packs of Tumerocks sending wave after wave of arrow winging towards me! Somehow, I survived. Down to 5 hitpoints, I finally found a spot where I could rest and heal. My buffs ran out as I caught my breath. Completley healed, I began a new buff cycle ... only to fizzle on the first try and burn out my last silver scarab!!! The Gods were having a grand jest at this Old Crow's expense! but, I was not going to give up! Throwing on all my jewlery, I was determined to press on. Putting arrow to string I took my first step...an awakened a Diamond golem in a shallow depression directly in front of me. I don't know why i did it, but I fired an arrow at the beast and then ran straight for him. My arrow found it's mark for only 3 points of damage, but the surprise of the arrow or the shock of me running at him must have thrown the golem off a bit as he just stode there as I zoomed past. A late blow was thrown my way but was way of the mark; the Strength Inept VI he threw next was right on! Running at a fast crawl pace with a Diamond Golem on my heals was not my idea of a fun day, but somehow I managed to elude the beast and took a seat to wait out the debuff. I was almost at the end of the landbridge and had evaded more critters than I had ever seen in all my runs. With the debuff gone I made ready to reach the end of the bridge and start my second leg. Following my plan, I started running through what appeared to be empty territory buut soon had a back of silver rats and several swarms of gold wasps on me. So far, I had managed to eveabe all their attacks and hit the end of the bridge. I turned south to the next ridge but the little beasts decided to pursue me. As i made the ridge I ran into a pack of Bone Lord skellies. With rats, wasps and skeelies all out for bllod I took the only avenue of escape available...I ducked into a nearby dungeon portal. I'm not sure what it is called but I think Dia has been here before. I am going to rest then head out on my second leg of this trip. after all...it can't get any worse ... right?!?!?!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>6:05:53 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=6><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">It got worse!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The ale here in Fort Teth is watered down! Hhahaahah..yup, made it...barely. I made the short run off the ridge by the Mountain Hall portal...yup, that is where I was it seems...and began the crosscountry run to the old tower and lifestone. Stupid me...I didn't look at the map and almost ran directly into a tumerock tower!! I corrected my mistake at the last second and veered further west to the tower I was searching for. Through packs of wasps, banderling strykers and enforcers I ran. I took debuff after debuff..later I would find 12 differant debuffs total..each with multiple layers..all V's and VI's! The last straw came when I ran into a pack of boneknights and took 2 hits from acid swords. I somehow managed to limp into my tower! I'm not sure how long I sat inside...but before my debuffs had elapsed I ran downstairs, hit the lifestone and ran for Fort Teth! I managed to dodge most of the critters and actually ran inot Teth at Full health. I'll lifestone as soon as my beer is gone and then take the Glendon Wods portal for some scarabs. Then I will plan my next move...the run to the Rim portal!! Wish me luck!!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>6:59:28 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=7><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">OK ... who let the umbris into the tavern?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Out of character: When I was growing up my uncle would sometimes pack me into his old stationwagon and drive us down to Boston Garden to see the Boston Bruins kick butt, take names and play a little hockey. We were both hugh Terry O'Reilly fans and while Terry was a good hockey player ... he was a great enforcer! Yup, that boy could fight. And back in those days knowing how to use your enforcers was just as important as scoring goals. Just about every &quot;incident&quot; Terry was involved in would end with the same two things ... terry in the penalty box and the other guy bleeding all over the ice. Of course, terry met his match on occasion .. like the islander's Clark Gillies. Terry and Clark had some epic battles and after each, in his worse Italian accent, my Uncle would turn to me and say, &quot;Now that's a spicey meatball!' i know, it sounds stupid...but it was funny at the time and a ripoff of some commercial back then that i can't recall now. Pretty soon, the diehard hockey fans in our row would always say the same thing after a good terry punch-up ... &quot;Now that's a spicey meatball!&quot; Hahahah...I know...stupid. <br>
Well, Crow just logged back in Fort Teth's alehouse to continue his journey but found himself watching a hugh war! It seems some choad let an Umbris follow him into the tavern! Luckly, Crow logged out over the bar so I watch the fight unfold. Already there were more bodies than I could count littering the floor. Spells were flying, arrows fired and weapons swinging...but the shadow was winning. A lifemage was outside draining through the wall, but the umbris hit the guy through the wall with his fist and killed him with 2 shots! I was cheering for the umbris!! Some little unarmed guy ran in and went toe to toe but soon died. he came back 3 more times and meet the same fate each time. I was laughing my butt off as people ran in...took a hit or two and then ran screaming for the hills. Sadly, it soon ended with the arrival of 3 mages who quickly drained the shadow down to a shadow of his former self. get it...shadow of his former self? Hhahahaha Anway...with the death of the shadow I looked around the room and all i could think of was ... &quot;Now THAT was a spicey meatball!&quot; I'm going to sudway for a meatball snadwich..back in a few and then I'll continue Crow's run.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>7:39:11 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=8><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: OK ... who let the umbris into the tavern?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Terry O'Reilly and the &quot;Big Bad Bruins&quot;... those were the days!<br>
<br>
This is fantastic Crow, I rushed home from work to catch the next installment!!! Keep the updates coming, I'm on the edge of my seat here!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>8:02:58 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=9><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Westward Ho!!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">By the way...westward ho is not an euphemism for a cowboy prostitute. Ahhh, as much as I love fall in New England ... fall is Texas has it's good points as well. Like...good looking babes at Subway dressed in shorts!!! Hubba hubba!! OK, got me a sand-mich, diet croke and a happy belly! time to leave Fort Teth and head west towards the rim portal!!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>8:06:09 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=10><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Skellie Lord - 1, Crow - 0</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Yup ... I died. Right outside of Teth too! Ran across a hidden skellie lord and he killed me in 1 shot...no debuffs, no melee ... just one acid spell to the back of me ol noggin and off to the lifestone I went. It was a clean kill and my hat is off to that skellie lord ... actually my hat is REALLY off as my helmet is still on my body. I'm gonna give them a few minutes to leave or get killed then go back. Hope I can get to my body as I think I died about 2 feet from a spawn point. Oh well....what's the Dires without a little death huh?</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>8:14:46 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=11><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Westward Ho!!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Me too Ghar! I was trying not to disturb the poet, but what the hell? GO CROW!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/30/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9:04:32 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=304.topic&index=12><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Think like a skellie ... be one with the skellie .</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well...I tried to be nice but Nooooooooo!! Stupid skellie wouldn't leave...even invited 2 friends to sit next to my corpse! OK...lets try the old shoot and scoot tactic. I'm an archer...I can shoot and I can run...kets teach these guys a lesson. NOT! I hit the skellie lord 1 time out of 20 for 28 points only. Lots of misses in there...but that is what saved me. About the 9th time the pack of ghouls ran aftr me I saw that they couldn't get back to their original spot. They were now several more feet away from my body hung up on my stray arrows. Death will make you miss sometimes...this time it was a blessing. I put on my skellie mask for good luck and slowly walked towards my corpse...1 step at a time. I was sweating bullets as I knew at any second they could turn and cut me down in a hail of spellfire!! Somehow...I actually made it!! They were so close I could actually hear them but they were not moving. maybe it was the mask...maybe luck...but I grabbed my gear and headed west at a fast jog!!<br>
